page.title: 10LANDSCAPE
page.content: The Gawsworth Landscape.A description of what the children can see around them in Gawsworth. North side of the school,we can see, Congleton road,Steven's Garage, sheep in a field and the school's cricket pitch. East side of the school,we can see the Old People's Estate and in the distance,the tail end of the Pennines, the G.P.O Tower and a house being built. South side of the school,we can see three shops,three evergreens which are called Noble Fir,two deciduous trees and the school's notice board. West side of school, we can see in the distance a Horse Chesnut Typed by Ben Lee, Steven Downs, and Kate Wilbraham.
